  &lt;/dcc:content&gt;
&lt;/drmd:instructionsForHandlingAndUse&gt;
</code></pre>

Cardinality CRM: Required / PIS: Optional (<code>[0..1]</code>) <p>Narrative traceability statement(s) linking the certified values back to the SI, reference standards, or calibration chains.</p> <p>Schematron Rule: RMC-001</p> <p>Reference Material Certificates (CRM profile) MUST include a <code>metrologicalTraceability</code> statement (ISO 33401:2024, §5.3.4).</p> <pre><code>&lt;drmd:metrologicalTraceability&gt;
  &lt;dcc:content lang="en"&gt;
    Certified values are metrologically traceable to the SI through calibrated mass
    standards and validated analytical methods as described in the certification report.
  &lt;/dcc:content&gt;
&lt;/drmd:metrologicalTraceability&gt;
</code></pre>

Cardinality Optional (<code>[0..1]</code>) <p>Safety guidance, hazard statements, and PPE requirements. Often includes an attached Safety Data Sheet (SDS).</p> <p>Schematron Rule: DRMD-015</p> <p>It is Recommended (Warning) to include <code>healthAndSafetyInformation</code> for both CRM and PIS profiles.</p> <pre><code>&lt;drmd:healthAndSafetyInformation&gt;
  &lt;dcc:content lang="en"&gt;
    Handle as metal alloy. Avoid inhalation of dust if machining. Use appropriate PPE.
    Refer to the attached Safety Data Sheet (SDS).
  &lt;/dcc:content&gt;
&lt;/drmd:healthAndSafetyInformation&gt;
</code></pre>

Cardinality Optional (<code>[0..1]</code>) <p>Narrative listing of subcontracted activities or contributing labs/organizations to provide transparency of the certification process.</p> <pre><code>&lt;drmd:subcontractors&gt;
  &lt;dcc:content lang="en"&gt;
    Selected measurements were carried out by subcontracted laboratories participating
